0 MAP MAPS~
Syntax: map
        map <map width up to 100>

The map command will allow how to see a text representation of the current
map around you in order to help visualize the layout of the terrain that
you're standing in.  It can be very handy when learning new areas and the
world.

~

0 SUICIDE DELETE~
Use the delete command to erase unwanted characters, so the name will be
available for use.  This command must be typed twice to delete a character,
and you cannot be forced to delete.  Typing delete with an argument will
return your character to 'safe' status if you change your mind after the
first delete.
~

0 TEMPLE HEALER~
The healer at the temple will provide spells for a donation of gold.  To
see a full listing of the healer's services type 'heal' in his presence.
To receive healing, bring plenty of money and type 'heal <spell>'.
~

0 GAIN CONVERT~
The gain command is used to learn new skills, once the proper trainer has 
been found. (Check New Thalos) The following options can be used with gain:

gain list:    list all groups and skills that can be learned
gain points:  lower your creation points by 1 (costs two sessions)
gain <name>:  add a skill or skill group, at the listed cost
gain convert: turns 10 practices into one training session

Gain uses training sessions, not practices. (see 'help train')
Gained skills and groups do NOT increase your experience per level or total
number of creation points.  The gain convert option can be enabled or 
disabled by the game administrators.
~

0 TEST MODE~
Test mode allows an immortal to turn on the testing mode for all users of
the mud without having to set or unset them automatically.  Test mode
provides additional logging and diagnostic messages for use when debugging
or testing.
~

0 LOGIN COLOR PROMPT~
This setting allows the mud administrator to toggle whether a new
connection to the mud will be prompted for whether they want color or
not.
~

52 CLONE~
Syntax:
  clone obj <object>
  clone mob <mobile>
  clone <name>

The clone command duplicates an object or mobile.  The level of item or mobile
that may be cloned depends on your level.  The target object or mob must be in
the same room as you, or in your posession.  Strung and set information is
preserved by clone, as well as any spell effects and container contents or
mobile inventory, except for items which are too high for you to clone.  
Strung extended descriptions on objects are not kept, however.
~

0 SKILLS SPELLS~
The skills and spells commands are used to display your character's list
of available skills (or spells, as the case may be).  They are listed in
order of level, with mana cost (for spells) or percentage (for skills)
listed where applicable.
~

0 OUTFIT~
The outfit command, usable by levels 5 and below, equips your character with
a new set of sub issue gear (banner, weapon, helmet, shield, and vest), 
courtesy of the Mayor's warehouses.  Only empty equipment slots are affected.
~

0 AUTO AUTOLIST AUTOLOOT AUTOGOLD AUTOSAC AUTOEXIT AUTOASSIST AUTOSPLIT AUTOALL~
This mud uses various automatic actions to ease the boredom of always splitting
gold and sacrificing corpses.  The commands are as follows:

autolist  : list all automatic actions
autoloot  : take all equipment from dead mobiles
autogold  : take all gold from dead mobiles
autosac	  : sacrifice dead monsters (if autoloot is on, only empty corpes)
autoexit  : display room exits upon entering a room
autosplit : split up spoils from combat among your group members
autoassit : makes you help group members in combat
autoall   : turns all autos on or off at once

Typing a command sets the action , typing it again removes it. Use
autoall on|off to save yourself some keystrokes.
~

0 CLAN~
A Clan is a collection of players, united to  follow and further
a common cause.   Each clan has rules and  regulations, to find out
more about clans and their 'beliefs' type "help <clan name>".  Only
Clan  members can kill or steal from other players.  To join a Clan
you  must be level 5 or above and level 25 or below.   Speak to the
Clan Leader about joining.  If you go Loner before level 25 you may 
join a Clan later.
   Joining  a  Clan is a dangerous step.   Many adventurers live to 
kill and torture others and chances are that your paths will cross.
Remember, attacking or killing fellow clan members *IS* illegal except to 
mutiny your Clan leader.
   Existing  Clans may buy  special rooms and  mobiles by acquiring 
diamonds as payment.   To see room prices, type "help prices".  New
Clans  may be formed by  petitioning the immortals.   Please  remember that 
their word is final on all matters not covered by this help.
~

0 PRICES PRICE~
New Clan Hall Rooms cost 50 diamonds.
Boosting the mana or healing gains for a room costs 250 diamonds.
Both in the same room costs double.
Making the Healer or Store prices lower costs 1,000 diamonds.
~

0 COUNT~
The count command displays the number of people (that you can see) logged
into the mud.  It also displays the highest number observed that day, if
it is higher.
~

0 GATE~
The gate spell is a powerful transportation magic that opens up a portal 
between your character and another person or creature somewhere else in the
world.  This portal will transport you and any pet you might have, but not
other members of your group.  Monsters recieve a save against gate, and
monster or players more than 3 levels higher than you can not be gated to at 
all.  God rooms, private rooms, and no recall rooms cannot be gated to, and
no recall rooms cannot be gated out of.  Finally, any god or hero is also 
immune to gate, as well as in player who has no summon set.  Clan members 
may not be gated to except by their fellow Clan members.
~

0 AFFECTS AFFECT~
This command is used to show all the spells affecting your character. At
low levels, only the spell name will be displayed, at higher levels the
effects and duration of the spell will also be shown.  Spell effects
are no longer shown on score (this can be changed by using 'show' command).
~

0 WITHERING ENCHANT~
Syntax: cast 'withering enchant' <object>

This spell allows an enchantor to magically wither an item so that it will
disintegrate when its bearer perishes
~

0 ENCHANT GEM~
Syntax: cast 'enchant gem' <object>

Enchant gem allows the enchantor to magically enhance an ordinary jewel so
that it has the properties of a warp stone. 
~

0 INTERLACE SPIRIT~
Syntax: cast 'interlace spirit' <object>

Interlace spirit allows an enchantor to interlace his/her own spirit into
the given weapon or piece of armor.  Interlace spirit does not remove
anything from the current object, but _does_ interlace your own spirit with
any other aura it already has.  
~

0 ENCHANT PERSON~
Syntax: cast 'enchant person' <victim>

Enchant person allows the enchantor to enchant a person's soul and imbue
their combat abilities.  Its strength can vary depending on the enchantor.
~

0 RESTORE WEAPON~
Syntax: cast 'restore weapon' <object>

The restore weapon spell allows the enchantor to return a weapon to its
orginal state.  The only requirement to restore an item is that its current
state has had an enchantment placed on it.  It has been rumoured that
attempting to restore a weapon does not always work out as expected, so at
times, enchantors may wish to be wary.  
~

0 RESTORE ARMOR~
Syntax: cast 'restore armor' <object>

The restore armor spell allows the enchantor to return a piece of armor to
its orginal state.  The only requirement to restore an item is that its
current state has had an enchantment placed on it.  It has been rumoured
that attempts to restore a piece of armor may not have the desired effects,
so enchantors may wish to be wary.  
~

0 DISENCHANT~
Syntax: cast 'disenchant' <item>

A disenchantment allows the enchantor to fade any magical effects that have
been placed on the weapon or armor.  It has been rumoured that this effect
is similiar to the effects of enchantment fading.  
~

0 WIZARD MARK~
Syntax: cast 'wizard mark' <object>

This spell scribes the mark of the caster into the targeted object.  To
determine whether some object in you inventory has been marked, one must
cast the spell of identification upon the object.  
~

0 SEQUESTOR~
Syntax:  cast 'sequestor' <object>

This spell allows an enchantor to make an item unable to be located.
~

0 DUAL WIELD~

Dual wield allows a fighter to wield two weapons at the same time
giving them additional attacks per round.
~

53 COPYOVER~
Syntax: copyover [now|delay <ticks>|cancel<reason>

Sample Usage: copyover now
              copyover now <reason>
              copyover delay 3
              copyover delay 3 <reason>
              copyover cancel

The copyover is also called a hot reboot.  It allows a newly compiled
version of the mud to be put into play while keeping all of the 
players connected.

~

52 IMMORTAL BLESSING WIZBLESS~
Syntax:  wizbless <character|all>

Allows a high level immortal to grant a single player or all players a
non cancellable or dispellable blessing.  This will increase various
stats and provide a few small bonuses for 120 ticks.

This should be used as a way to thank players who are logged in.
~

0 SPELLCRAFT~

Spellcraft is a speciality skill available to mages and most mage
reclasses.  It gives the caster the ability to know what spells others
are casting.  It also allows the caster to regenerate more mana as
well as (and most importantly) cast one level higher.
~

0 LOCATE WIZARD MARK~
This spell is a specialized locate object spell.  It allows the 
enchantor with high detail and a high success rate to locate items 
that they have wizard marked by their hand.
~

0 LOCATE BIND~
The locate bind spell will allow the caster to locate the room and
area that bind stones are in throughout the entire world.
~

0 CLEAR~
The clear command will clear the screen on mud clients that support it.
~

0 STATS~
Syntax: stats
        stats brief

Shows your current stats (strength, intelligence, wisdom, dexterity
and constitution) along with adjustments from spells and equipment
that might raise it.

The stats command will also show you the max stats your race/class
combo can achieve.

You can see a brief compacted version of the stats by additionally
including a brief after the command (stats brief).
~

0 SWIM~
The ability to swim will allow the person to move about in water
that previously required a boat.  Crimson Skies has both ocean
and underwater areas and not knowing how to swim will quickly
result in drowning.  

Those who swim should take caution, if you run out of movement
in the ocean you will start to lose health even if you are an
excellent swimmer.  All players have the ability to swim by
default.
~

0 WHOAMI~
Syntax:  whoami

"Who am I" will show you the name of the character you are
currently logged in as.

~

0 RECLASS~
Syntax: reclass <reclass name>

The reclass command will allow you to train as a specialized class.  Each
base class will have certain classes which it can reclass into (for
instance, a mage can reclass into an enchantor but a warrior cannot).

You must be at least level 10 to reclass.  The higher the level you are
the more trains and practices you will start off with when you 
reclass (e.g. a level 51 character will have more initial trains and
practices than a level 10 character after the reclass).

After reclass you will be level 1 again as the reclass.

Current classes available for reclass:

   {G*{x Enchantor (Mage)
   {G*{x Healer (Cleric)
   {G*{x Bladesinger (Any class, elves only)
   {G*{x Ranger (Warrior & Thieves)
   {G*{x Rogue (Thieves)
~

0 WAVES OF WEARINESS~
A spell where enchantors charm an individual to sleep causing them
to release any weapons they maybe wearing.
~

0 HEALER~
Healers are masters of healing ailments, health and other aspects
of individuals.  Many of their spells and skills focus on supporting
other individuals.

See also:  reclass
~

0 SACRIFICIAL HEAL~
Sacrificial heal allows the healer to fully heal an individual although
at great cost to their own health.
~

0 MASS REFRESH~
Refreshes the movement of all individuals in the room unless they are
hidden.
~

0 VITALIZING PRESENCE~
A healing spell that will heal small bits of health to the affected
over an extended period of time.
~

0 ENHANCED RECOVERY~
A healer spell that will help the recipient gain back more health, 
mana and movement during their normal healing process.
~

0 HEALERS BIND~
The healers bind spell allows a skilled healer to create a bind stone
that can stay in a room.  When other characters touch the bind stone
they will be both healed and refreshed.  When a bind stone has used
all of it's energy it will fade out of existence.

Only one bind stone is allowed to exist in an area at any given time.
~

0 LIFE BOOST~
A healing spell that allows a healer to increase the health (HP) of
an individual for a period of time.
~

0 MAGIC RESISTANCE~
Magic resistance allows a healer to boost an individuals resistance
to offensive magic spells.
~

0 MANA TRANSFER~
Mana transfer is a spell that allows healers to transfer some of
their magically energy to another individual.  It can considered
the mana equivalent of a heal.
~

0 CURE WEAKEN~
The cure weaken spell will allow a healer to cure a weaken spell
with great precision.
~

0 CURE DEAFNESS~
The cure deafness spell allows a healer to cure players who are
inflicted with deafness either by skill or spell.  
~

0 CURE SLOW~
The cure weaken spell will allow a healer to cure a weaken spell
with great precision.
~

0 REMOVE FAERIE FIRE~
A curative spell mastered by healers to remove the effects of
faerie fire on an individual.
~

0 RESTORE MENTAL PRESENCE~
The restore mental presence spell will allow a healer to remove
any stun affect they have on themselves.
~

0 SENSE AFFLICTION~
The sense affliction spell will allow healers to see any
individuals in a room that are affected by a spell that
they can heal.  If the healer examines the individual they
will specifically see what is afflicting the person.
~

0 NOURISHMENT~
The nourishment spell allows a healer to nourish a person removing all
hunger and thirst.
~

0 GUILDLIST~
Syntax: guildlist

The guildlist command will show you basic information about the clans and 
kingdoms available to join and any additional information know about them.
~

52 GUILD~
Syntax: guild <character> <clan name>
        guild <character> none

The guild command allows an immortal to guild a player into a clan.  If
the immortal wishes to remove the player from a clan they can use the
word 'none' for the clan name and it will un-guild them.
~

0 CLASS~
Syntax: class
        class <class name>

The class command will give you information about all of the classes and reclasses
available in Crimson Skies.  It will provide you with the class name, whether it's
a base class or reclass, the who name, the primary stat of the class, whether the
class casts spells at level and how high their skill adept is set (which is how
high they can practice the skill at a trainer).  The detailed view by specifying
the class you want to view will provide you with all of the publically available
information.
~

0 SKILL ADEPT~
A classes skill adept is how high a player can train their skills at a trainer.
The base classes have a skill adept of 75%.  There are some reclasses that will
have a higher skill adept at around 85%.
~

0 KENDER~
Adult Kender resemble young teenage humans: Aside from their pointed ears,
they could pass as human youths.  Despite their attenuate limbs, kender are
well-muscled.  Most stand between 3'6" and 3'9" tall, although some few grow
to be up to four and a half feet.  Mature kender weigh between 85 and 105
pounds.  Typically, kender faces bear the intense, bright-eyed
inquisitiveness of children.  Happy kender grin madly; sad kender wear an
intractable pout.  When throwing taunts, kender look impish and shout in an
incredibly grating tone.  Their emotional intensity is infectious.  In their
countless pouches, pockets, and belt packs, kender carry a wide assortment
of junk.  Kender of all ages share a childlike nature: curious, fearless,
irrepressibly independent, lazy, taunting, and irresponsible with others
possessions.  

Kender receive pick lock for free due to it being one of a kender's most
passionate hobbies.  They receive pick lock and peek as they are cherished 
hobbies of theirs that feed their unmatched curiosity.  Kender additionnaly
receive sneak, hide and dodge for being lightfooted and agile.
~

0 MINOTAUR~
Minotaurs resemble a human bull hybrid with the body of a very strong
human and the head of a bull with horns.  They are honorable and proud
creatures who walk both the good and evil paths.  Their horns give them
the unique racial ability to charge at a victim (gore).
~

0 WORLD MIDGAARD ARCANIS CONTINENT~
The world is currently split up into multiple continents.  The old world
continent of Midgaard is named after it's largest kingdom Midgaard.  The
continent of Midgaard lays in the western seas.  The continent of Arcanis
lays in the eastern seas.

Travel through the ocean is harsh, many rely on portals from mages both
temporarly and permanent to traverse the world quickly.
~

0 BLADESINGER~
The Bladesinger is an elite fighter, skillfully combining magic and
might to defeat his foes, and the foes of all elves.  The Bladesinger is a
rarely multi-classed mixture of Mage and Warrior, effective using his spells
to augment his swordarm.  Bladesingers are most effective in combat when
dancing the bladesong an art that has been passed down through the elven
generations.

See also:  reclass
~

0 BLADESONG~
The Bladesong is at the core of a bladesingers power.  A bladesinger trained
in the art of the bladesong is said to both hit more accurately and harder.  It's
ritual also allows the bladesinger to cast a group of spells called the bladesongs.
The bladesinger further dodges better and hits more while dancing the bladesong.
They may not however use any weapons other than a sword of dagger and the removal
of those weapons either by their own accord or being disarmed will cease the
beneficial affects from it.

Bladesongs:

 - Song of Protection
 - Song of Dissonance
~

0 SONG OF PROTECTION~
The song of protection is a bladesong that will protect the bladesinger defensively 
as well as any of their group members.  The bladesinger must first be dancing the
bladesong in order to cast this spell.
~

0 SONG OF DISSONANCE~
The song of dissonance is a bladesong that pierces the ears of enemies that render
their hearing useless for a short duration.  It is directed in a manner that allows
the bladesinger to avoid hitting their group members.
~

0 CIRCLE~
The circling tactic is a manuever of the Bladesong in which the bladesinger
nimbly disorients the victim by quickly circling them.  It's been told that
though all bladesingers learn this method, that full blooded elves are often
just slightly more profiecient in it's movements.
~

0 CIRCLE STAB~
The circle stab is a technique that a bladesinger can use on targets that have
already been disoriented by circling.  If successful the bladesinger will gain
an additional two hit attempt in a round as well as potentially dealing a
stunning blow although the circumstances must be just right for that.  As with
all bladesinger skills, they must be dancing the bladesong first to attempt
this.
~

0 BLIND FIGHTING~
The blind fighting skill allows warriors to fight better while blind than they
otherwise would have.  This advantage pertains to all blindness, magical and
physical (a blind spell, dirt kicking).
~

0 SETTINGS~
Syntax: settings
Syntax: settings <setting to change> <optional value>

The settings command allows a player to see the current game settings that
are in play (this includes things for locks, features and game mechanics).

As an immortal of a high enough level you can use the settings command to
additionally change the game settings.
~

0 DOUBLE EXPERIENCE~
Double experience is an optional setting a game admin can turn on that will
give players double the experience for the duration that the setting is on.
This is typically something an admin might turn on for a special occasion.
~

0 DOUBLE GOLD~
Double experience is an optional setting a game admin can turn on that will
give players double the gold haul for the duration that the setting is on.
This is typically something an admin might turn on for a special occasion.
~

0 KILL MURDER~
The 'kill' command will allow you to attack an in game creature (referred
to as a mob).  The 'murder' command will allow you to attack another game
player given that the player is within 8 levels of you and is a clanner.
~

0 SCAN~
Syntax: scan
Syntax: scan <direction>

The scan command (without an argument) will show you all visible players
to you who are currently in the room with you or are only one room away.
If you include a direction with scan (such as 'scan north') you will peer
in that direction and you will be able to see visible players and
creatures as far as 3 rooms away.
~

0 TOUCH~
Syntax: touch <object or player>

The touch command simply allows you to touch another player or object.
In most cases, this won't have any affect but there are certain objects
that can be triggered by touching them (healer's binds, certain buttons,
and other magical items).
~

0 WORTH~
Syntax: worth

The worth command will show you the amount of money that you own as well
as give you information about how much experience you currently have.
~

0 COMBINE~
Syntax: combine

Toggles whether you have item combining turned on.  Item combining will
determine how you see you see objects individually in your inventory or
see them combined with a total count:  e.g.

    Inventory:
        A mithril ring
        A mithril ring

    vs.

    Inventory
        (2) A mithril ring

~

0 NOFOLLOW~
Syntax: nofollow

Toggles whether you allow other people to follow you or not.  If you turn
nofollow on while someone is following you then they will be forced to
stop following you.  If you lead a group and turn nofollow on the group
will be dissolved.
~

0 NOLOOT~
Syntax: noloot

Toggles whether or not you allow looting on your corpse after you die.  If
you do not have looting turned on you will also not be allowed to loot
other players.  This only pertains to pkill situations.
~

0 NOSUMMON~
Syntax: nosummon

Toggles whether or not you allow other players to summon you with magic.
If this is toggled on, other players will not be able to cast the summon
spell and transport you across the world.
~

0 TELNETGA~
Syntax: telnetga

"Telnet go ahead" is a protocol which in which the server sends a packet
to the client telling it that it is ok to start sending data back.  This
is likely not needed with most modern clients (modern being anything
newer than the mid 90's).
~

0 QUIET~
Syntax: quiet

The quiet command will toggle on and off quiet mode.  Quiet mode will
silence all channels.  You will still see things that are happening
in the room you are in and also hear people talking to you in the
current room.

When you are in quiet mode the who list will indicate to other players
via a [Quiet] tag that you cannot hear channels.
~

0 DIRECT~
Syntax: direct <player> <what you want to say>
        > <player> <what you want to say>
        @ <player> <what you want to say>

Direct, '>' or '@' will allow you to say something directly to a player
who is in the same room.  All other players in the room will see that
you have directect the say at that individual.  Example:

> Isaac hello, how are you.

You see:
    You say (to Isaac) 'hello'
The room sees:
    Rhien says (to Isaac) 'hello'
Isaac sees:
    Rhien says (to you) 'hello'
~

0 SHOW~
Syntax: show

Toggles whether affects will show in the score command.
~

0 SURRENDER~
Syntax: surrender

Attempts to surrender to an enemy in order to stop a battle.
~

0 ENTER~
Syntax: enter <portal>

The enter command will allow you to step into a portal which in turn
will transport you somewhere else in the realm.
~

0 LAND~
Syntax: land

The 'land' command will cause you to float to the ground if you are
currently affected by the fly spell or are floating.
~

52 VIOLATE~
Syntax: violate <vnum>
        violate <player name>

The violate command will allow an immortal of a high enough level to
goto a player or a vnum of a room that is private and doesn't normally
allow other players.
~

52 NOCHANNELS~
Syntax: nochannels <player name>

The 'nochannels' command (nochan for short) is a penalty that allows
an immortal to take channel access away from a player.  The player
can still hear all channels but will no longer be allowed to speak
on them.
~

52 BROADCAST~
Syntax: broadcast <message>

The broadcast command will send a message to all players AND people
connected to the MUD.  This means they will see the message in active
playing state, in creation, at the login prompt, etc.  The command
will also display your name and will be heard whether a player is
sleeping, in quiet mode or deaf, etc.  It cannot be ignored.

[Broadcast from Rhien]: We will be implementing new areas in the next hour.
~

52 PREFIX~
Syntax: prefix

The 'prefix' command will toggle whether or not you see a prefix set of
characters before wiznet messages.  E.g.

Rhien has logged in.

vs.

--> Rhien has logged in.

~

52 FORCETICK~
Syntax: forcetick

The 'forcetick' command forces the processing of a tick and all tick
related logic out of the normal 40 second cycle.  This should only
be used by coders or implementors who know what they are doing and
have a specific purpose for it (like testing).
~

52 RENAME~
Syntax: rename <old name> <new name>

Renames a character.
~

52 VNUMGAP~
Syntax: vnumgap room
        vnumgap obj
        vnumgap mob

The 'vnumgap' command will show you all vnums not assigned to an area.
~

52 PATHFIND~
Syntax: pathfind <character>

Pathfind is an immortal command that will attempt to give you the
shortest path to a given character or mob in the area you are in.
This can be helpful when mapping out directions to get to places
that you might want to share on a web page or wiki.

~

52 TEST~
Syntax: test

The test command toggles whether you are in tester mode or not.
If you are in tester mode you (or a player if they are set via
the set command) will be denoted with a (Tester) flag and will
see additional information throughout the game (for instance,
how much damage each attack makes, etc.).  Testers also do not
timeout and disconnect.  It should *only* be used on players
currently testing.
~

52 WIZCANCEL~
Syntax: wizcancel <character>

The wizcancel command will cancel ALL affects on a player.  This
is mainly used for testing and also to remove affects that maybe
broken or added via a bug that aren't cancellable.
~

0 GORE~
Syntax: gore <character>

Gore is a technique used by the minotaur race in which they are
able to charge and ram a victim with their horns.  All minotaurs
of all classes have this ability by default.
~

0 GHOST~
Upon dying to either a player or a creature you will become a
ghost for a short period of time.  Ghosts can not attack or be
attacked.  It is said that they float and take on a transparent
appearance able of passing through doors.

~

0 PORTAL MERCHANT~
A portal merchant is a merchant who will create portals for you
to other parts of the world for a price.  The price generally
will cost more if you're wanting a portal that spans continents.
The portal the merchant creates will only last for a few moments.
~

52 PORTAL~
Syntax: portal <vnum>
        portal <vnum> <optional tick duration>
        portal <player name/mob name>
        portal <player name/mob name> <optional tick duration>

The portal command allows an immortal to create a portal to a
specific vnum, a player, a mob or an object (in that order).
An optional numeric value for duration can be provided if the
immortal wants the portal to disappear after a set number of
ticks.  Portals created with this command will always be
purgable.

~

0 DIG BURY~
Syntax:  dig
Syntax:  bury

Bury will allow you to take an object and bury it in the ground.
The ground must be soft enough for an object to be buried.  Small
objects can be buried with your hands but larger objects will
require the use of a shovel.

Digging up objects also requires the ground is soft enough to
dig (so city streets won't be diggable, but fields will).  You
can dig with your hands but will find it much faster to dig with
a shovel.  If you interrupt your digging with another action you
will have to start over digging.
~

52 CONFISCATE~
Syntax: confiscate <item> <player>

Confiscate will take an item from a player and put it in the
immortal's inventory.  If the item is equipped on the player it
will be unequipped.

The player is given notice that this has occurred.
~

0 TERRAIN~
Syntax: terrain

The terrain command will show you what the surrounding terrain
is (e.g. hills, forest, city, ocean, underwater, beach, etc.).
~

0 ACUTE VISION~
A character skilled in acute vision is able to see creatures
that are either sneaking or hiding in the immediate area.
~

0 RANGER~
Rangers are warriors who are associated with the wisdom of nature.
They tend to be wise, cunning, and perceptive in addition to being
skilled woodsmen. Many are skilled in stealth, wilderness survival,
beast-mastery, herbalism, and tracking.  They are adept at swordplay
and fight much better in a wilderness setting.  Rangers typically have 
keen eye sight and are excellent at hiding in forest areas.  

See also:  reclass
~

0 BUTCHER~
The butcher skill allows rangers to prepare edible steaks from the 
remains of creatures.
~

0 BANDAGE~
The bandage skill allows a healer, a cleric or a ranger the ability to
bandage critically injured players.  This can restore small amounts of
health that might save a person's life.  The skill will put a tax on the
players movement in order to perform it.
~

0 BARK SKIN~
Syntax: cast 'bark skin'

The bark skin spell allows one who posses the nature spell group to
turn the texture of one's skin into a hard bark like one.  This spell
can only be cast on yourself.
~

0 SELF GROWTH~
Syntax: cast 'self growth'

The self growth spell is one of the nature spell group which allows a
ranger to raise their constitution slightly.  This spell can only be
cast on one's self.
~

0 QUIET MOVEMENT~
Syntax:  qmove

Allows a skilled ranger to move undetected through many various
wilderness terrains.
~

0 CAMP CAMPING~
Syntax: camp

Camping is a skill that allows rangers to setup camp and gain additional
regeneration while in forests, fields, hills, deserts or the mountains.
Any player who is grouped with the ranger while they are camping will also
receive the regeneration bonus.  Camping is interrupted when the ranger
leaves the current room, is attacked or attacks someone or quits the game.

Regeneration benefits from camping are greater when camping at night than
during the day.
~

0 CAMOUFLAGE~
Syntax: camouflage

Camouflaging allows a ranger to hide in various wilderness settings.
Camouflage is similiar to hide although it will not break if other commands
are performed EXCEPT movement.  A ranger must be camouflaged in order to
ambush other people.
~

0 TRACK~
Syntax: track <target name>

The track skill allows a ranger to locate the general direction of a target
whether that be a player or a creature in the game.  
~

57 CRYPT~
Syntax: crypt <player name> <password>

Creates a encrypted hash based off of a player's name and a password.  This
can be placed into a players pfile to reset a password (require's access to
the player files on the server).  Name is case insenstive, password is case
sensitive.
~

0 RANDOMNAMES~
Syntax: randomnames

The random names command will show a set of random names that you can use
for character names.  These names will be checked against existing player
files to make sure they are all available for use.
~

0 FIND WATER~
Syntax: findwater

Find water is a skill that allows rangers to search for water in most
outdoor and wilderness areas.  It will not work inside, in cities or
in deserts.
~

0 STANCE~
Syntax: stance <offensive|defensive|normal>

The stance command allows you to take a strategic battle stance in
combat.  The following are the specific advantages and
disadvantages:

Normal:     No bonus or penalty.
Offensive:  Chance for an extra attack every round of combat and a
            higher chance of hitting.  The penalty is a slightly lower
            chance of dodging, parrying or shield blocking.
Defensive:  Chance to lose an attack every round and a slightly lower
            chance of hitting.  The bonus is a greater chance of
            dodging, parrying or shield blocking.
~

0 FOG~
Syntax: cast 'fog'

The fog spell allows a caster to create a fog in a room.  Other people
traveling through the room may not be able to see well in that room
until the fog lifts.  The fog spell typically does not take as well
in city areas.  The fog created only last for a few moments.

SEE ALSO: dispel fog
~

0 DISPEL FOG~
Syntax: cast 'dispel fog'

The dispel fog spell will allow a caster to dispel a fog in a room
restoring visibility to all who pass through it.

SEE ALSO: fog
~

52 CLEARREPLY~
Syntax: clearreply <player name>

The clear reply command will clear the last person who sent you a
message so they will no longer be able to reply.  This can useful
if an immortal wants to go wizinvis or incognito and stop a player
from being able to reply.
~

0 POISON PRICK~
Syntax: poisonprick <victim>

Poison prick is a skill unique to the Rogue class where the rogue
with a high chance of success attempts to prick a victim with a
poisoned needle.  The poison causes less severe effects than a
poison spell but can be stacked on top of it.

Healer's can cure this poison via the cure poison spell.
~

0 SHOCK SPREAD~
While underwater, weapons of a shocking or lightning nature will
cause additional damage to creatures and players you may fight.

Shock spread is a game wide setting that will allow the immortals
to change the behavior of the shock so that it can spread to other
mobs and cause damage.  You can see if it's toggled on in the
settings command.
~

0 KNOCK~
Syntax: knock <direction>
        knock <door name>

Knocking on a closed door allows any characters on the other side of
the door to hear the knocking (letting them know that someone is there
and wants in).
~

0 LONER~
Syntax: loner <your name>

The loner command will allow any player to become a loner in the clanned
system providing that they are between level 5 and 25 and are not already
the member of a clan.

In order to go loner after level 25 you must be guilded by an immortal
who will require you to purchase a voucher.
~

0 REVOLT~
Syntax: revolt <victim>

Revolt allows a rogue to incite a victim to turn on their master.  This
might be a pet like a horse, a hired assassin, an elemental or it might
be a player that is charmed.  The victim once inciting will intiate
combat against their previous master.
~

0 BLUDGEON~
Syntax: bludgeon <victim>

Bludgeon is a skill rogue's have mastered that allow them to temporarly
stun and lower the intelligence and wisdom of a victim.  The bludgeon
skill requires that the rogue be wearing a mace.
~

0 IMBUE~
Syntax: c 'imbue'
        c 'imbue' <target>

Imbue is a clerical spell in the benedictions group that allows for a
cleric to raise the casting level of themselves or another for a short
period of time.
~

0 CANCEL COMMAND TILDE~
This mud offers the ability to cancel commands which have been entered
but not processed yet.  In order to do this you can send a tilde
character in your input at anytime.

As a practical example, you may have spammed 2 or 3 bash commands in
which take 3 rounds of combat to fulfil.. using tilden you can cancel
the 2nd and 3rd in order to enter new commands in their place (such
as re-arming a weapon if you are disarmed).
~

58 PLAYERLIST~
Syntax: playerlist

Lists all players who have a file in the player file storage
directory.  This could be a lengthy list depending on the size
of the player base.
~

0 PRESERVE~
Syntax: cast 'preserve' <object>

The preserve spell will allow an enchantor to stop an object from
rotting or crumbling over time, such as after a death when the rot
death flag has been invoked.  This spell causes a great deal of
stress on the enchantor who will have to wait after they cast it
in order to cast it again.
~

60 PERMANENT~
Syntax: permanent <object name>

A high level immortal command that makes any temporary affects on an
object permanent.  This can be used to create unique quest items for
instance that make a bless or fireproof last forever.
~

0 QUEST PQUEST~

syntax:  pquest request
         pquest info
         pquest complete
         pquest clear
         pquest reset (Immortal only)

There are quest masters in most cities who are able to assign personal       
quests for characters.  When in the presence of this person, you can
request a personal quest using the syntax shown above.  The quest master
in Midgaard (the most popular spot) is two north of recall.

While on a quest, you may use the "info" syntax to get a reminder of what
the goal of your quest is.  

When you have completed the assigned quest, you must return to the mob that
assigned the quest and use the "complete" syntax to obtain your reward.  
There is a short time delay between quests.

If you feel that you are unable to complete a quest in the time allocated or
feel that it is beyond your ability to complete use the "clear" syntax to
clear the quest.  Of course, the questor will not be to pleased with you.  

Personal quest rewards come in the form of gold and quest points.  Quest
points are shown in your score and may be saved up and used to purchase
special items from the quest mob.  
~

